# Platform Profile: Microsoft Copilot

**Provider:** Microsoft (powered by OpenAI models)  
**Interface:** Microsoft 365 (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook, Teams), GitHub Copilot, Bing, Windows  
**Two distinct surfaces:** M365 Copilot (productivity) and GitHub Copilot (coding)

---

## Strengths
- Deepest Microsoft 365 integration of any platform — reads and writes Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook, Teams natively
- GitHub Copilot: strongest repo-integrated code completion and PR review
- GitHub Copilot coding agent: Claude Sonnet 4.6-powered, operates on actual GitHub repos
- Enterprise-grade security, compliance, and data governance (SOC 2, HIPAA, GDPR)
- Works within existing Microsoft tenant — no data leaves the org boundary
- Teams integration: meeting summaries, action items, follow-up drafts
- Strong for business document generation within the M365 ecosystem

## Weaknesses
- Outside M365/GitHub context: less capable than Claude or ChatGPT for open-ended tasks
- Bing Chat (consumer Copilot) is more limited than enterprise M365 Copilot
- Less precise instruction-following than Claude for complex structured tasks
- Custom configuration options are more limited than Claude or ChatGPT API

## Context Window
- M365 Copilot: document-scoped (entire Word/Excel file)
- GitHub Copilot: repo-scoped with selective file loading
- Behavior: context is defined by the file or repo being worked on, not a token limit the user manages

## Memory & Persistence
- **M365:** Work persists naturally in SharePoint, OneDrive, and Exchange
- **GitHub Copilot:** Repo state is the persistent context; `.github/copilot-instructions.md` provides persistent configuration
- **No cross-app memory** by default — context is scoped to the current file or repo
- **Handoff note:** For M365 work, share the file link. For GitHub work, reference the repo and branch.

## System Prompt Support
- ✅ GitHub Copilot: `.github/copilot-instructions.md` in the repo root
- ✅ M365 Copilot: system-level configuration via Microsoft 365 admin center
- ⚠️ Consumer Copilot (Bing): limited system prompt control

## Tool Availability
- Microsoft 365 apps (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook, Teams, OneNote — native)
- GitHub repo operations (PR review, issue management, code generation)
- Bing web search (native)
- Azure integrations
- Microsoft Graph API access (enterprise)
- Power Platform connectors (enterprise)

## Prompt Format Conventions
- For M365 tasks: reference the document or data directly rather than describing it
- For GitHub tasks: reference files, functions, and PRs by path/name
- Works well with plain language instructions; less dependent on structured formatting
- In Teams: prompts are conversational — keep them brief and action-oriented
- For `.github/copilot-instructions.md`: use concise, declarative rules

## Ideal Task Types
- Microsoft 365 document work (Word reports, Excel models, PowerPoint decks)
- Outlook email drafting, summarization, and response within M365
- Teams meeting summaries and action item extraction
- GitHub PR review, issue triage, and code generation within a repo
- Enterprise tasks with strict data governance requirements
- Any work where staying inside the Microsoft tenant is a compliance requirement

