## Handoff Receiving Template

### For M365 Copilot

```
=== COPILOT (M365) HANDOFF PACKAGE ===
Project: [name]
Handed off from: [platform] ([phase])
Receiving: Microsoft Copilot in [Word / Excel / PowerPoint / Outlook / Teams]

[Open the relevant M365 file, then use Copilot within that app]

Document/file: [SharePoint or OneDrive link]

Context: [2-sentence description of the project and what's needed]

Task: [Specific instruction for what Copilot should do with this document]
- [Action 1]
- [Action 2]

Constraints:
- [Style/format requirements]
- [Content constraints]

Re-entry: When complete, export/save the document and run:
/handoff return from Copilot
Include: link to updated document, summary of changes made

=== END ===
```

### For GitHub Copilot

```
=== COPILOT (GITHUB) HANDOFF PACKAGE ===
Project: [repo name]
Branch: [branch name]
Handed off from: [platform] ([phase])
Receiving: GitHub Copilot ([phase])

[Add to .github/copilot-instructions.md before starting:]

## Current Task
[What Copilot is being asked to do]

## Conventions
[Code style, naming, patterns to follow]

## Do Not Modify
[Files or directories that must not change]

## Context
[2-sentence project description]

---

[In GitHub Copilot chat or agent:]

Continue work on [project]. What has been done: [summary].
Your task: [explicit instruction with file references].
Constraints: [hard limits].

When done, output: files changed, decisions made, blockers.

=== END ===
```

## Configuration Checklist
- [ ] M365 Copilot: confirm Copilot license is active for the tenant
- [ ] M365: open the target document before invoking Copilot
- [ ] GitHub Copilot: confirm `.github/copilot-instructions.md` is updated
- [ ] GitHub: confirm correct branch is checked out
- [ ] Enterprise: confirm data governance policies allow the task type
